				<td colspan="2"><span>ive dueled my wife (65 bst with elem geared, 7k hps, resists hit 2-300) she made bard paste out of me when i was 56.  once i made 65 and had my essential spells, we dueled again...several times now, this is what i've learned (blue server info) 
<br />
first the pet has some ungodly resists, cannot be charmed (its a lvl 60 war if they have the biggest pet), mez almost never lands, even with HoS.
<br />
I tried to run the pet to the other side of the zone, hopeing that i could beat it back to her....didnt work, pet auto returns when i get to far away from her, which she even said was weird.
<br />
i had some luck with highsun (it shadow steps and removes a buff), but only landed sometimes with HoS
<br />
I had a blast with HoS/mez/mana drain on the player (not pet), just keep moving or the pet gets you.
<br />
have DA ready, beastlords have some massive  dmg discs, really is nice to let them waste to a DA bard, hehe
<br />

<br />
so whats the answer to dueling a beast? h*ll if i know, im still trying to beat her, shes a 7k hp dmg class with a 4.5k hp pet that quads for 79, flurries and procs a DD/stun.  my best attempt was mez/mana drain then getting a pet of my own (i used a dorf when we dueled in the great divide...but only because she was working dorf faction for the shawl quest, so she didnt want to kill it), the pet will pay it no attention...unless its less than 20%...ive tried to develop some sort of strat out of that and charmed pets that are low on life...gives you 15-20 seconds of no pet bites.  
